Java implementation of the CoAP protocol (draft 18)
===================================================
see: http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-core-coap-18

Draft-18 is the one to become an RFC at sometime, i.e. there are (if any) only few and minor changes expected in the
future. This implementation currently only supports the main protocol (without extensions like observe).


Maven
=====

To use the latest SNAPSHOT nCoAP Maven artifact add the following to your pom.xml

<repositories>
...
    <repository>
        <id>itm-maven-repository-snapshot-site</id>
        <url>https://maven.itm.uni-luebeck.de/content/repositories/snapshots/</url>
    </repository>
...
</repositories>

....

<dependencies>
...
    <dependency>
        <groupId>de.uniluebeck.itm</groupId>
        <artifactId>ncoap</artifactId>
        <version>1.8.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    </dependency>
...
</dependencies>


Documentation
=============

The documentation is available at http://media.itm.uni-luebeck.de/people/kleine/maven/ncoap/

To get started with using the nCoAP framework I refer to https://github.com/okleine/SimpleCoapApplications.
